<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7517> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7517" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "In MRR 2.307, delete the name of the Caecilius listed as a tribune of the plebs in 45. He was apparently an architect and in any case had first seen Rome less than two years before (Shackleton Bailey, CLA 5.381; cf. Att. 13.20, 33a.4, and 35.1).\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5884> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5884" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "He introduced bills for Caesar's program to beautify the plan of the city (Cic. Att. 13.20.1, and 33a.4, and 35.1, gentilis tuus; cf. Suet. Iul. 44; Dio 43.49). His office is not named, but he was almost certainly a Tribune since no Praetors were elected until Caesar's return from Spain early in September. See Niccolini, FTP 344." .
